icity and disrespect: a parodic or amusing tone surrounds him as he refers or is referred to aspects of his traditional image. The great characters of the Poem give two wise responses to Zeus, lord of destiny: "heroic death" or serene acceptance. We, the readers, are expected to react in the same way.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aEpic poetry, GreekxHistory and criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aIliad.  aZeus.  adestiny.  a heroism.  a myth.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2018 Part 1z978311076248808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2018z978311071955008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2018 Englishz978311060400908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2018z9783110603095oZDB-23-DGD0 cEPUBz97831106015410 cprintz978311060137440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311060245640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110602456423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110602456/original  a978-3-11-060400-9  EBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060425-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-071955-0  DG Plus eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-076248-8  DG Plus DeG Package 2018 Part 1b2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGDb2018  aZD